For a **Project Pulse AI – Delivery Governance Agent**, the suggested prompts should feel like questions a Project Manager, Team Lead, Scrum Master, or Delivery Manager would actually ask.

## 1. Project Status Overview

**Title:** Project Status Summary

**Message:**

> Show the current status of all active projects, including progress, health score, open risks, blockers, and upcoming milestones.

---

## 2. Project Health Check

**Title:** Project Health Score

**Message:**

> Calculate the project health score and explain the key factors affecting the score, including delays, risks, blockers, and pending approvals.

---

## 3. Overdue Tasks

**Title:** Overdue Task Analysis

**Message:**

> Show all overdue tasks, task owners, due dates, project names, and recommended actions to resolve delays.

---

## 4. Risk Assessment

**Title:** Project Risk Report

**Message:**

> Identify current project risks, severity levels, business impact, owners, and recommended mitigation actions.

---

## 5. Release Readiness Review

**Title:** Release Readiness Check

**Message:**

> Assess release readiness by reviewing testing status, documentation completion, approvals, open defects, and security sign-offs.

---

## 6. Meeting Action Items

**Title:** Meeting Action Summary

**Message:**

> Extract decisions, action items, owners, due dates, and follow-up actions from the latest meeting notes or transcript.

---

## 7. Weekly Project Report

**Title:** Weekly Governance Report

**Message:**

> Generate a weekly project governance report including project status, completed work, delayed activities, risks, blockers, and recommendations.

---

## 8. Delayed Activities

**Title:** Delayed Activities Review

**Message:**

> Identify all delayed activities across projects and provide the reason, owner, impact, and recovery recommendations.

---

## 9. Open Blockers

**Title:** Blocker Analysis

**Message:**

> Show all open blockers, impacted projects, responsible owners, expected resolution dates, and associated risks.

---

## 10. Resource Workload Review

**Title:** Resource Utilization

**Message:**

> Analyze project assignments and identify team members with overloaded workloads or multiple overdue tasks.

---

## 11. Approval Bottlenecks

**Title:** Approval Status Review

**Message:**

> Identify pending approvals, approval owners, aging duration, and any approvals that may impact delivery timelines.

---

## 12. Executive Project Dashboard

**Title:** Executive Summary

**Message:**

> Provide an executive-level summary of project performance, risks, release readiness, overdue work, and key management actions required.

---

## 13. Upcoming Milestones

**Title:** Milestone Tracker

**Message:**

> Show upcoming project milestones, planned completion dates, dependencies, and any risks affecting milestone delivery.

---

## 14. Project Risk Prediction

**Title:** Delivery Risk Forecast

**Message:**

> Analyze current project conditions and identify activities that may cause future schedule or delivery risks.

---

## 15. Assigned Action Items

**Title:** My Assigned Actions

**Message:**

> Show all action items assigned to me, their status, due dates, priority levels, and any overdue work.

---

## 16. Governance Compliance Check

**Title:** Governance Review

**Message:**

> Verify whether project governance requirements, approvals, documentation, and reviews have been completed.

---

## 17. Release Approval Status

**Title:** Release Approval Tracker

**Message:**

> Show the status of all release approvals and identify any pending sign-offs that may delay deployment.

---

## 18. Project Manager Daily Brief

**Title:** Daily Delivery Brief

**Message:**

> Summarize today's project activities, overdue tasks, risks, blockers, approvals, and critical actions requiring attention.

---

### Best 4 to Display on the Agent Home Screen

1. **Project Status Summary**
2. **Project Health Score**
3. **Weekly Governance Report**
4. **Release Readiness Check**

These four immediately demonstrate the agent's value during a live showcase or manager demo.
